---
@version: [current]
@description: Create a HTML comment.
@lot: string $content = "", int $dent = 0, $block = false
@static: 1
@example: |
  echo HTML::comment('This is an example of inline comment.');
  echo HTML::comment('This is an example of block comment.', 0, true);
  echo HTML::comment('This is an example of indented block comment.', 1, true);
@result: |
  [[e]]echo HTML::comment('This is an example of inline comment.') . "\n\n" . HTML::comment('This is an example of block comment.', 0, true) . "\n\n" . HTML::comment('This is an example of indented block comment.', 1, true);[[/e]]
@result-language: 'html'
@result-note: |
  If for a reason, you want to create a HTML `<comment>` tag, you can use [this][link:unite] method:

  ~~~ .php
  echo HTML::unite('comment', 'Content goes hereâ€¦');
  ~~~
